# Framer Motion — FromSoftware Animation System

## Core Rule
Never hardcode duration or easing values. All presets live in `@/lib/motion/fromSoftware`.

```ts
import { fsMotion } from "@/lib/motion/fromSoftware";
```

---

## fsMotion API Reference

### Easing
```ts
fsMotion.ease // [0.33, 0, 0.17, 1] — canonical. Deep ease-out, no bounce.
              // Alternative for longer entries: [0.43, 0.13, 0.23, 0.96]
              // Scroll-snap programmatic: [0.22, 1, 0.36, 1] duration 1.5s
```

### Durations (`fsMotion.dur.*`)
```ts
fsMotion.dur.reveal       // 1.05s — scroll reveal entries
fsMotion.dur.headline     // 1.05s — hero headings
fsMotion.dur.route        // 0.82s — route transitions
fsMotion.dur.chrome       // 0.88s — header / footer
fsMotion.dur.background   // 2.1s  — background image fade-in
fsMotion.dur.loginShell   // 1s    — login container
fsMotion.dur.loginField   // 0.76s — login inputs
```

### Y Offsets (`fsMotion.px.*`)
```ts
fsMotion.px.reveal   // 10px  — scroll reveal
fsMotion.px.title    // 10px  — headings
fsMotion.px.login    // 14px  — login panel
fsMotion.px.headerY  // -5px  — header entry (moves down into place)
```

### Staggers (`fsMotion.stagger.*`)
```ts
fsMotion.stagger.headline  // 0.22s — between heading lines
fsMotion.stagger.navGap    // 0.26s — between nav links
// Generic list stagger: 0.1s minimum between children
```

### Hero Intro (`fsMotion.homeIntro.*`)
Full choreography for the home hero. Use as-is, don't override individual values.

---

## Patterns

### Standard entry (opacity + y)
```tsx
const reduce = useReducedMotion();

<motion.div
  initial={reduce ? false : { opacity: 0, y: fsMotion.px.reveal }}
  animate={reduce ? false : { opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: fsMotion.dur.reveal, ease: fsMotion.ease }}
/>
```

### Staggered list
```tsx
const reduce = useReducedMotion();

<motion.ul
  initial="hidden"
  animate="visible"
  variants={{ visible: { transition: { staggerChildren: 0.1 } } }}
>
  {items.map(item => (
    <motion.li
      key={item.id}
      variants={{
        hidden: reduce ? {} : { opacity: 0, y: fsMotion.px.reveal },
        visible: { opacity: 1, y: 0, transition: { duration: fsMotion.dur.reveal, ease: fsMotion.ease } },
      }}
    />
  ))}
</motion.ul>
```

### Scroll reveal — always use the wrapper
```tsx
import { Reveal } from "@/components/motion/Reveal";

<Reveal>
  <p>Lore content</p>
</Reveal>
```
Never re-implement scroll reveal logic inline. Always use `<Reveal>`.

### Route transition (template.tsx)
```tsx
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1 }}
  exit={{ opacity: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: fsMotion.dur.route, ease: fsMotion.ease }}
>
  {children}
</motion.div>
```

### Background image fade
```tsx
<motion.div
  initial={reduce ? false : { opacity: 0 }}
  animate={reduce ? false : { opacity: 0.55 }}
  transition={{ duration: fsMotion.dur.background, ease: fsMotion.ease }}
  className="absolute inset-0"
>
  <Image src="..." alt="" fill priority className="object-cover" />
</motion.div>
```

### Ambient particles / embers / fog
Use CSS animations, not Framer Motion. Keeps the main thread free.
```css
@keyframes ember-float {
  0%   { transform: translateY(0) translateX(0); opacity: 0; }
  50%  { opacity: 0.6; }
  100% { transform: translateY(-120px) translateX(20px); opacity: 0; }
}
.ember { animation: ember-float 4s ease-in-out infinite; }
```

---

## ✅ Allowed
- `opacity` + `y` as entry properties (max 20px offset)
- `scale` only for micro hover interactions (`whileHover={{ scale: 1.02 }}`)
- Stagger via `staggerChildren` in variants
- CSS animations for particles, fog, and looping ambience

## ❌ Prohibited
- `spring` type (any bounce perception)
- `bounce` or `elastic` on any property
- `scale` as a page or section entry animation
- Duration < 0.7s on page-level animations
- `x` as a primary entry axis
- Framer Motion built-in named easings (`"easeOut"`, `"easeInOut"`) without custom curve

---

## Reduced Motion — Non-Negotiable
Every animated component must respect `useReducedMotion()`:

```tsx
import { useReducedMotion } from "framer-motion";
const reduce = useReducedMotion();

// Use `false` (not `{}`) to skip animation — avoids flash
initial={reduce ? false : { opacity: 0, y: fsMotion.px.reveal }}
```

Using `{}` instead of `false` still runs the animation. Always use `false`.

---

## Global Config
`AppMotionConfig` in `@/components/AppMotionConfig.tsx` wraps the app with `<MotionConfig>`.
Do not add another `<MotionConfig>` wrapper. Override at component level via `transition` props only.
